17#include <config.h>

19#include <ctype.h>
20#include <stdbool.h>

28typedef struct elt {
29 char * key;
30 unsigned int type;
31 isc_symvalue_t value;
32 LINK(struct elt) link;
33} elt_t;
34
35typedef LIST(elt_t) eltlist_t;
36
37#define SYMTAB_MAGIC ISC_MAGIC('S', 'y', 'm', 'T')
38#define VALID_SYMTAB(st) ISC_MAGIC_VALID(st, SYMTAB_MAGIC)
39
40struct isc_symtab {
41 /* Unlocked. */
42 unsigned int magic;
43 isc_mem_t * mctx;
44 unsigned int size;
45 unsigned int count;
46 unsigned int maxload;
47 eltlist_t * table;
48 isc_symtabaction_t undefine_action;
49 void * undefine_arg;
50 bool case_sensitive;
51};
52
53isc_result_t
54isc_symtab_create(isc_mem_t *mctx, unsigned int size,
55 isc_symtabaction_t undefine_action,
56 void *undefine_arg,
57 bool case_sensitive,
58 isc_symtab_t **symtabp)
59{
60 isc_symtab_t *symtab;
61 unsigned int i;
62
63 REQUIRE(mctx != NULL);
64 REQUIRE(symtabp != NULL && *symtabp == NULL);
65 REQUIRE(size > 0); /* Should be prime. */
66
67 symtab = (isc_symtab_t *)isc_mem_get(mctx, sizeof(*symtab));
68 if (symtab == NULL)
69 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
70
71 symtab->mctx = NULL;
72 isc_mem_attach(mctx, &symtab->mctx);
73 symtab->table = (eltlist_t *)isc_mem_get(mctx,
74 size * sizeof(eltlist_t));
75 if (symtab->table == NULL) {
76 isc_mem_putanddetach(&symtab->mctx, symtab, sizeof(*symtab));
77 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
78 }
79 for (i = 0; i < size; i++)
80 INIT_LIST(symtab->table[i]);
81 symtab->size = size;
82 symtab->count = 0;
83 symtab->maxload = size * 3 / 4;
84 symtab->undefine_action = undefine_action;
85 symtab->undefine_arg = undefine_arg;
86 symtab->case_sensitive = case_sensitive;
87 symtab->magic = SYMTAB_MAGIC;
88
89 *symtabp = symtab;
90
91 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
92}
93
94void
95isc_symtab_destroy(isc_symtab_t **symtabp) {
96 isc_symtab_t *symtab;
97 unsigned int i;
98 elt_t *elt, *nelt;
99
100 REQUIRE(symtabp != NULL);
101 symtab = *symtabp;
102 REQUIRE(VALID_SYMTAB(symtab));
103
104 for (i = 0; i < symtab->size; i++) {
105 for (elt = HEAD(symtab->table[i]); elt != NULL; elt = nelt) {
106 nelt = NEXT(elt, link);
107 if (symtab->undefine_action != NULL)
108 (symtab->undefine_action)(elt->key,
109 elt->type,
110 elt->value,
111 symtab->undefine_arg);
112 isc_mem_put(symtab->mctx, elt, sizeof(*elt));
113 }
114 }
115 isc_mem_put(symtab->mctx, symtab->table,
116 symtab->size * sizeof(eltlist_t));
117 symtab->magic = 0;
118 isc_mem_putanddetach(&symtab->mctx, symtab, sizeof(*symtab));
119
120 *symtabp = NULL;
121}
122
123static inline unsigned int
124hash(const char *key, bool case_sensitive) {
125 const char *s;
126 unsigned int h = 0;
127 int c;
128
129 /*
130 * This hash function is similar to the one Ousterhout
131 * uses in Tcl.
132 */
133
134 if (case_sensitive) {
135 for (s = key; *s != '\0'; s++) {
136 h += (h << 3) + *s;
137 }
138 } else {
139 for (s = key; *s != '\0'; s++) {
140 c = *s;
141 c = tolower((unsigned char)c);
142 h += (h << 3) + c;
143 }
144 }
145
146 return (h);
147}
148
149#define FIND(s, k, t, b, e) \
150 b = hash((k), (s)->case_sensitive) % (s)->size; \
151 if ((s)->case_sensitive) { \
152 for (e = HEAD((s)->table[b]); e != NULL; e = NEXT(e, link)) { \
153 if (((t) == 0 || e->type == (t)) && \
154 strcmp(e->key, (k)) == 0) \
155 break; \
156 } \
157 } else { \
158 for (e = HEAD((s)->table[b]); e != NULL; e = NEXT(e, link)) { \
159 if (((t) == 0 || e->type == (t)) && \
160 strcasecmp(e->key, (k)) == 0) \
161 break; \
162 } \
163 }
164
165isc_result_t
166isc_symtab_lookup(isc_symtab_t *symtab, const char *key, unsigned int type,
167 isc_symvalue_t *value)
168{
169 unsigned int bucket;
170 elt_t *elt;
171
172 REQUIRE(VALID_SYMTAB(symtab));
173 REQUIRE(key != NULL);
174
175 FIND(symtab, key, type, bucket, elt);
176
177 if (elt == NULL)
178 return (ISC_R_NOTFOUND);
179
180 if (value != NULL)
181 *value = elt->value;
182
183 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
184}
185
186static void
187grow_table(isc_symtab_t *symtab) {
188 eltlist_t *newtable;
189 unsigned int i, newsize, newmax;
190
191 REQUIRE(symtab != NULL);
192
193 newsize = symtab->size * 2;
194 newmax = newsize * 3 / 4;
195 INSIST(newsize > 0U && newmax > 0U);
196
197 newtable = isc_mem_get(symtab->mctx, newsize * sizeof(eltlist_t));
198 if (newtable == NULL)
199 return;
200
201 for (i = 0; i < newsize; i++)
202 INIT_LIST(newtable[i]);
203
204 for (i = 0; i < symtab->size; i++) {
205 elt_t *elt, *nelt;
206
207 for (elt = HEAD(symtab->table[i]); elt != NULL; elt = nelt) {
208 unsigned int hv;
209
210 nelt = NEXT(elt, link);
211
212 UNLINK(symtab->table[i], elt, link);
213 hv = hash(elt->key, symtab->case_sensitive);
214 APPEND(newtable[hv % newsize], elt, link);
215 }
216 }
217
218 isc_mem_put(symtab->mctx, symtab->table,
219 symtab->size * sizeof(eltlist_t));
220
221 symtab->table = newtable;
222 symtab->size = newsize;
223 symtab->maxload = newmax;
224}
225
226isc_result_t
227isc_symtab_define(isc_symtab_t *symtab, const char *key, unsigned int type,
228 isc_symvalue_t value, isc_symexists_t exists_policy)
229{
230 unsigned int bucket;
231 elt_t *elt;
232
233 REQUIRE(VALID_SYMTAB(symtab));
234 REQUIRE(key != NULL);
235 REQUIRE(type != 0);
236
237 FIND(symtab, key, type, bucket, elt);
238
239 if (exists_policy != isc_symexists_add && elt != NULL) {
240 if (exists_policy == isc_symexists_reject)
241 return (ISC_R_EXISTS);
242 INSIST(exists_policy == isc_symexists_replace);
243 UNLINK(symtab->table[bucket], elt, link);
244 if (symtab->undefine_action != NULL)
245 (symtab->undefine_action)(elt->key, elt->type,
246 elt->value,
247 symtab->undefine_arg);
248 } else {
249 elt = (elt_t *)isc_mem_get(symtab->mctx, sizeof(*elt));
250 if (elt == NULL)
251 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
252 ISC_LINK_INIT(elt, link);
253 symtab->count++;
254 }
255
256 /*
257 * Though the "key" can be const coming in, it is not stored as const
258 * so that the calling program can easily have writable access to
259 * it in its undefine_action function. In the event that it *was*
260 * truly const coming in and then the caller modified it anyway ...
261 * well, don't do that!
262 */
263 DE_CONST(key, elt->key);
264 elt->type = type;
265 elt->value = value;
266
267 /*
268 * We prepend so that the most recent definition will be found.
269 */
270 PREPEND(symtab->table[bucket], elt, link);
271
272 if (symtab->count > symtab->maxload)
273 grow_table(symtab);
274
275 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
276}
277
278isc_result_t
279isc_symtab_undefine(isc_symtab_t *symtab, const char *key, unsigned int type) {
280 unsigned int bucket;
281 elt_t *elt;
282
283 REQUIRE(VALID_SYMTAB(symtab));
284 REQUIRE(key != NULL);
285
286 FIND(symtab, key, type, bucket, elt);
287
288 if (elt == NULL)
289 return (ISC_R_NOTFOUND);
290
291 if (symtab->undefine_action != NULL)
292 (symtab->undefine_action)(elt->key, elt->type,
293 elt->value, symtab->undefine_arg);
294 UNLINK(symtab->table[bucket], elt, link);
295 isc_mem_put(symtab->mctx, elt, sizeof(*elt));
296 symtab->count--;
297
298 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
299}
300
301unsigned int
302isc_symtab_count(isc_symtab_t *symtab) {
303 REQUIRE(VALID_SYMTAB(symtab));
304 return (symtab->count);
305}
